articles.title: Private hospital fee benchmarks: Will more transparency lower healthcare bills?
articles.content: Health Minister Ong Ye Kung earlier this month announced plans to benchmark additional private hospital charges beyond the professional fees already covered, including surgeon, anaesthetist and inpatient attendance fees. Speaking on CNA's Deep Dive podcast, Mr Ong said benchmarking surgeon fees has proven "quite effective", with most charges now falling within the recommended range. Besides professional fees, existing Ministry of Health (MOH) benchmarks also cover hospital fees such as room charges, surgical facilities and equipment, and medication.
